cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper discusses machine learning algorithms, specifically autoencoders, for feature fusion and dimensionality reduction. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Given the focus on machine learning and feature fusion, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. However, the discussion of image datasets and computer vision techniques suggests that cs.CV is also a strong possibility. The inclusion of guidelines for choosing the proper autoencoder model and discussion of software tools suggests a focus on practical applications, which could be relevant to cs.AI and cs.SD. Finally, the use of neural networks and nonlinear combinations of features suggests a connection to cs.NE.
